article.headline: Middle Tennessee 90, Austin Peay 70
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Marcos Knight scored 16 points and led five Middle Tennessee players in double figures in the Blue Raiders' 90-70 win over Austin Peay Saturday night. The Blue Raiders (6-1), who never trailed, led 38-30 at halftime before opening the second half on a 15-2 run. LaRon Dendy's layup capped the run, and put them up 53-32 with 16:22 remaining. Austin Peay, which shot 36.2 percent for the game (21 of 58), was 1 of 8 during the spurt. Middle Tennessee shot 64.7 percent for the game (33 of 51), including a 7 of 14 effort from 3-point range, and outrebounded the Governors 40-26. Dendy and Shawn Jones finished with 13 points each, Kerry Hammonds 12 and Jason Jones 10 for the Blue Raiders. TyShawn Edmondson paced the Governors (0-7) with 14 points and Melvin Baker chipped in 12. Austin Peay trailed by as many as 22, with 50 seconds left.
